<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1394,1769]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,332,1433,1459]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[342,566,1433,1458]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lophomilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="striatipurpurea">
<emphasis box="[342,566,1433,1458]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">L. striatipurpurea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[584,676,1433,1459]" captionStart="FIGURES 33 – 39" captionStartId="17.[151,269,1781,1805]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,197,1756]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,197,1757]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 33 – 39. Lophomilia spp. and Hepatica anceps, adults and male genitalia. 33. L. striatipurpurea, imago (after Holloway 1976); 34. L. striatipurpurea, male genitalia (after Holloway 1976); 35. L. albicosta, China, Tapaishan, prep. 2093 VK ZFMK; 36. L. kobesi, holotype, prep. 6540 GB, Indonesia, Sumatra (ZSM); 37. L. violescens, holotype, Nepal (after Yoshimoto 1993); 38. L. albistria, prep. 6526 GB, Nepal, Kathmandu, Pulchouki Mt. (ZSM); 39. Hepatica anceps, Russia, Primorye terr. prep. AM ZISP." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/274664/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Fig. 
<number box="[644,676,1433,1459]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="33.0">33</number>
</figureCitation>
) “resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[842,1003,1433,1458]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lophomilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flaviplaga">
<emphasis box="[842,1003,1433,1458]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">L. flaviplaga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs in the proximity of the postmedial to the antemedial line on dorsum; lacks yellow tinge to dorsum of 
<taxonomicName box="[1056,1204,1472,1498]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lophomilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flaviplaga">
<emphasis box="[1056,1072,1472,1497]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1086,1204,1472,1497]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">flaviplaga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName box="[1220,1369,1472,1497]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lophomilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flaviplaga">
<emphasis box="[1220,1369,1472,1497]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">L. flaviplaga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lacks pale striations on veins and is generally redder in tint” (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Holloway" box="[862,1050,1511,1537]" pageId="16" pageNumber="22" refString="Holloway, J. D. (1976) Moths of Borneo with special reference to mount Kinabalu. Kuala Lumpur. San U. Book Co., 264 pp." type="book" year="1976">
Holloway 
<number box="[986,1050,1511,1537]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1976.0">1976</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Wingspan 
<quantity box="[1198,1330,1511,1537]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" metricValueMax="2.8" metricValueMin="2.6" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="mm" value="27.0" valueMax="28.0" valueMin="26.0">26–28 mm</quantity>
. Judging from the illustration in the original description (
<figureCitation box="[730,820,1549,1575]" captionStart="FIGURES 33 – 39" captionStartId="17.[151,269,1781,1805]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,197,1756]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,197,1757]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 33 – 39. Lophomilia spp. and Hepatica anceps, adults and male genitalia. 33. L. striatipurpurea, imago (after Holloway 1976); 34. L. striatipurpurea, male genitalia (after Holloway 1976); 35. L. albicosta, China, Tapaishan, prep. 2093 VK ZFMK; 36. L. kobesi, holotype, prep. 6540 GB, Indonesia, Sumatra (ZSM); 37. L. violescens, holotype, Nepal (after Yoshimoto 1993); 38. L. albistria, prep. 6526 GB, Nepal, Kathmandu, Pulchouki Mt. (ZSM); 39. Hepatica anceps, Russia, Primorye terr. prep. AM ZISP." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/274664/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Fig. 
<number box="[787,820,1549,1575]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="34.0">34</number>
</figureCitation>
), the structure of male genitalia is ancestral for the genus. All genitalia structures slender, the valva slightly constricted submedially, with small sacculus, saccular extension short and weak; clasper longitudinal, harpe not expressed. Aedeagus vesica lightly spined with a patch of broader spines. The female is unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1394,1769]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,517,1704,1730]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Distribution and biology.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[534,625,1704,1730]" captionStart="FIGURES 58 – 62" captionStartId="20.[151,270,1495,1519]" captionTargetBox="[193,1394,162,1465]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[151,1436,155,1471]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 58 – 62. Lophomilia spp., distribution maps. 58. L. albistria; 59. L. violescens; 60. L. striatipurpurea; 61. L. diehli; 62. L. kobesi." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/274667/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Fig. 
<number box="[591,625,1704,1730]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="60.0">60</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<collectingCountry box="[647,761,1704,1730]" name="Malaysia" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
: Borneo, Sabah, Kinabalu Mt. The single specimen was collected in July (
<date box="[359,497,1743,1769]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1965-07-15">
<number box="[359,389,1743,1769]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="15.0">15</number>
.vii. 
<number box="[432,497,1743,1769]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1965.0">1965</number>
</date>
). The larvae and foodplant are unknown.
</paragraph>
